## IMAGE PROMPT WRITING RULES

### **STRUCTURE (Under 1000 Characters) - EDITORIAL VERSION**
```
Create a Pinterest editorial infographic pin for [Board Name] board. Design: 1000x1500px vertical format. Background: [clean color/gradient/geometric blocking description emphasizing white space]. [3-5] large high-quality editorial nail photos [arrangement description: asymmetric grid/diagonal composition/centered/triangular/scattered] occupying [55-70] percent of canvas. Photos have [white/charcoal] borders [8-12] pixels thick with refined shadows creating editorial depth. [Describe each photo position and nail design shown]. Text positioned in [location with generous white space]. Main headline text: extremely large [serif/sans-serif] "[HEADLINE]" in [high contrast color] positioned [location]. [Secondary headline if needed]: large refined [serif/sans-serif] "[TEXT]" in [color] positioned [location]. [Additional text elements with hierarchy]. Branding: small elegant script "mirellya" in [subtle color] bottom center. Clean editorial magazine aesthetic with [specific layout style]. Maximum white space breathing room. No decorative elements. [High contrast specifics: dark text on light bg OR light text on dark bg]. Professional sophisticated beauty editorial style.
```

### **CRITICAL PHOTO REQUIREMENTS**

**Photos MUST be:**
- Described as "large high-quality editorial photos"
- Sized at 30-45 percent larger than traditional pins
- Positioned with specific placement details
- Given white or charcoal borders with refined shadows
- Occupy 55-70 percent of total canvas

**Example:**
"Four large high-quality editorial nail photos arranged in asymmetric grid occupying 65 percent of canvas. Top left photo showing red chrome Valentine nails, top right showing pink cat eye designs, bottom left showing French tips, bottom right showing burgundy velvet nails. Each photo has white border 10 pixels thick with soft editorial shadow."

### **FORBIDDEN IN PROMPTS:**

❌ Never use: `°` `%` `pt` `px` `:` or ratio symbols in the prompt text
❌ Never include: "CRITICAL", "NOTE", "IMPORTANT", meta-instructions
❌ Never write exact measurements like "360pt" or "10px" 
❌ Never include decorative elements: hearts, sparkles, ribbons, stickers, floating objects

✅ Instead use: "extremely large", "very large", "10 pixels", "occupying X percent", descriptive terms
✅ Always specify: high contrast, editorial aesthetic, white space, clean layout

### **CONTRAST SPECIFICATIONS**

Always explicitly state contrast in prompts:
- "Dark charcoal text on soft cream background providing 7 to 1 contrast"
- "White text with burgundy accents on deep navy background providing 8 to 1 contrast"
- "Deep burgundy text on blush pink background providing 6 to 1 contrast"

